<HEADLINE>
Sri Lanka tourist arrival slumped by 11 pct in 2007
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, Jan. 11 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's overall tourism arrival figures in 2007 slumped by 11
percent over 2006, the tourism authority said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
494,008 tourists arrived in Sri Lanka in 2007 compared with to
the arrival of 559,603 tourists in 2006, Sri Lanka Tourism said
in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The island's tourism industry has been affected by the upsurge in
violence in the separatist armed conflict in the embattled north
and east regions since the end of 2005.
</P>
<P>
Some Western nations have issued travel warnings to their
citizens due to the worsening peace and order situation in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Tourism said they are making efforts to improve the
negative image of the island projected abroad due to violence in
the civil war. At least 5,500 people have died in various
violence in the country.
</P>
